<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="face-n">face <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /feɪs/    美 /feɪs/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>脸；面部；面部表情：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a weather-beaten / smiling face 
饱经风霜的脸/笑脸</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I turned around and saw a pleasant woman <strong>with a</strong> big <strong>smile on</strong> her <strong>face</strong>.
我转过身来，看见一个面带笑容、和蔼可亲的女士。</p><footer>2016 全国</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>人：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There are a few <strong>new / different faces</strong> in class this year. 
今年班上来了几个新面孔。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>表面；坡面：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A cube has six faces. 
立方体有六个面。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the <strong>north face</strong> of the mountain
山的北坡</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>（事物的）特征：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The glaciers are disappearing,changing the face of Kilimanjaro.
冰川正在消失，改变着乞力马扎罗山的地貌。</p><footer>2019全国</footer></div>

<h4 id="5-faced">5.★ <strong>[构成形容词 -faced] 有…面容的；有…表情的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a round-faced / serious-faced girl
圆脸/表情严肃的女孩</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>red-faced
尴尬的；羞愧的</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="a-long-face">a long face</h3>
<p>1.<strong>愁眉苦脸：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Why do you <strong>have such a long face</strong>?
你为什么哭丧着脸？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— I lost my new cell phone.
我的新手机丢了。</p></div>

<h3 id="face-to-face">face to face</h3>
<p>1.<strong>面对面地 :</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I have often dreamed of talking face to face with you.
我一直希望和你当面聊一聊。</p><footer>2008 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He came face to face with a new problem.
他面临一个新问题。</p></div>

<h3 id="face-up-down">face up / down</h3>
<p>1.<strong>面朝上/下</strong>  </p>
<h3 id="in-the-face-of">in the face of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>面对；不顾：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He remained calm even in the face of danger.
即使面对危险，他也镇定自若。</p></div>

<h3 id="lose-face">lose face</h3>
<p>1.<strong>丢脸；失面子：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She was afraid of losing face if she failed.
她害怕如果失败会很没面子。</p></div>

<h3 id="make-pull-a-face-faces">make / pull a face / faces</h3>
<p>1.<strong>做鬼脸：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The boys made faces at each other when the teacher turned her back.
老师转过身去的时候，孩子们互相做鬼脸。</p></div>

<h3 id="to-sbs-face">to sb's face</h3>
<p>1.<strong>当着某人的面：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They called Tony “Fatty” but never to his face.
他们叫托尼“胖子”,但从未当面叫过他。</p></div></div>